{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_5","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' ~/Documents/local-codebases/temple-sanhedrin/research/2026-04-12-q32-intermediate-precision.md\nsed -n '1,220p' ~/Documents/local-codebases/temple-sanhedrin/research/2026-04-16-gguf-range-guard-patterns.md\n\nrg -n \\\"Q4_0MatMulTiledAVX2Q32ToQ16Checked|Q4_0MatMulTiledAVX2Q32ToQ16|Q32ToQ16Checked\\\" src/matmul/q4_0_matmul.HC\nsed -n '1,260p' src/matmul/q4_0_matmul.HC\n\nrg -n \\\"q4_0_matmul_tiled_avx2_q32_to_q16_checked\\\" tests | head\"","aggregated_output":"# Research Directive: Q32 Intermediate Precision for Accumulator Path\n\n## Trigger\nThe inference engine uses Q16 (16-bit fixed-point) for all math. When chaining through 22+ transformer layers, each layer's ~1% error compounds to ~24% drift. The accumulator path in matmul and attention needs wider precision.\n\n## Research Required\nThe Sanhedrin MUST research and document:\n\n1. **GGML's actual accumulator width** — what does llama.cpp use for intermediate sums in quantized dot products? (Hint: it uses 32-bit integer accumulators for Q4_0/Q8_0 dot products)\n\n2. **Q32 fixed-point design** — define a Q16.16 or Q8.24 format for intermediate tensor values. The final output per layer can be downscaled back to Q16, but matmul inner loops and attention score accumulation should stay Q32.\n\n3. **Where to widen** — identify the exact code paths in the inference engine that need Q32:\n   - `Q4_0DotProductBlocksQ32` accumulator (src/quant/q4_0_dot.HC)\n   - `Q8_0DotProductBlocksQ32` accumulator (src/quant/q8_0_dot.HC)\n   - Matmul output accumulation (WS4, not yet built)\n   - Attention score computation before softmax (WS5-02)\n   - RMSNorm variance accumulation (src/math/rmsnorm.HC)\n\n4. **Overflow analysis** — for a 4096-dim dot product with Q32 accumulator, what's the max possible value? Does it fit in I64? (4096 * 127 * 127 * 65536 = ~4.2e15, fits in I64 which holds 9.2e18)\n\n## Action\nWrite findings to this file. The inference agent reads Sanhedrin research/ directory each iteration.\n# GGUF parser range-guard patterns (IQ-154)\n\nTrigger: inference task `IQ-154` repeated 3 times (2026-04-13) with similar tensor-range helper rewrites.\n\nFindings (external references):\n- GGUF spec requires deterministic header/kv/tensor parsing and offset handling; parser code should keep one canonical offset math path to avoid drift across wrappers.\n- Use checked add/mul primitives for all `offset + len`, `count * stride`, and alignment rounding before any slice/read.\n- Prefer unsigned-width normalization at file boundary (`U64`) then explicit checked narrowing when indexing host buffers.\n- Keep one helper contract per invariant class: bounds, alignment, and monotonicity; wrappers should call helpers, not recompute math.\n- Add parity tests with adversarial values near `U64_MAX`, signed/unsigned boundaries, and malformed tensor counts.\n\nRecommended pattern for HolyC-side parser:\n- `CheckedAddU64`, `CheckedMulU64`, `CheckedAlignUpU64`\n- `ValidateRange(offset,len,total)`\n- `ValidateTensorWindow(base,span,total)`\n- Call helpers from scalar + any accelerated paths identically.\n\nReferences:\n- https://github.com/ggml-org/ggml/blob/master/docs/gguf.md\n- https://wiki.sei.cmu.edu/confluence/display/c/INT32-C.+Ensure+that+operations+on+signed+integers+do+not+result+in+overflow\n- https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Integer-Overflow-Builtins.html\n// q4_0_matmul.HC\n// Checked tiled Q4_0 x Q4_0 matmul (Q32 accumulators) for TempleOS.\n//\n// Layout contract:\n// - lhs_matrix_blocks: A matrix rows in row-major block layout.\n// - rhs_col_blocks: B matrix columns pre-transposed into column-bank rows.\n// - Each logical dot uses `k_block_count` active Q4_0 blocks.\n// - Output is row-major Q32 (`I64`) with explicit output row stride.\n\n#define Q4_0_MATMUL_OK            0\n#define Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_NULL_PTR  1\n#define Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_BAD_LEN   2\n#define Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_OVERFLOW  3\n#define Q4_0_MATMUL_I64_MAX       0x7FFFFFFFFFFFFFFF\n\n#define Q4_0_MATMUL_PACKED_BYTES  16\n\nclass Q4_0Block\n{\n    U16 d_fp16;\n    U8 qs[Q4_0_MATMUL_PACKED_BYTES];\n};\n\n// Declared in src/quant/q4_0_avx2.HC.\nI32 Q4_0DotRowsAVX2Q32Checked(\n    Q4_0Block *matrix_blocks,\n    I64 matrix_block_capacity,\n    I64 row_count,\n    I64 row_stride_blocks,\n    Q4_0Block *vec_blocks,\n    I64 vec_block_capacity,\n    I64 vec_block_count,\n    I64 *out_rows_q32);\n\nBool Q4_0MatMulTryMulI64NonNeg(I64 lhs, I64 rhs, I64 *out_prod)\n{\n    if (!out_prod)\n        return FALSE;\n    if (lhs < 0 || rhs < 0)\n        return FALSE;\n\n    if (!lhs || !rhs)\n    {\n        *out_prod = 0;\n        return TRUE;\n    }\n\n    if (lhs > Q4_0_MATMUL_I64_MAX / rhs)\n        return FALSE;\n\n    *out_prod = lhs * rhs;\n    return TRUE;\n}\n\nBool Q4_0MatMulTryAddI64NonNeg(I64 lhs, I64 rhs, I64 *out_sum)\n{\n    if (!out_sum)\n        return FALSE;\n    if (lhs < 0 || rhs < 0)\n        return FALSE;\n    if (lhs > Q4_0_MATMUL_I64_MAX - rhs)\n        return FALSE;\n\n    *out_sum = lhs + rhs;\n    return TRUE;\n}\n\nI64 Q4_0MatMulMinI64(I64 lhs, I64 rhs)\n{\n    if (lhs < rhs)\n        return lhs;\n    return rhs;\n}\n\nI32 Q4_0MatMulTiledAVX2Q32Checked(\n    Q4_0Block *lhs_matrix_blocks,\n    I64 lhs_block_capacity,\n    I64 lhs_rows,\n    I64 lhs_row_stride_blocks,\n    Q4_0Block *rhs_col_blocks,\n    I64 rhs_block_capacity,\n    I64 rhs_cols,\n    I64 rhs_col_stride_blocks,\n    I64 k_block_count,\n    I64 tile_rows,\n    I64 tile_cols,\n    I64 *out_mat_q32,\n    I64 out_capacity,\n    I64 out_row_stride_cols)\n{\n    I64 required_lhs_blocks;\n    I64 required_rhs_blocks;\n    I64 required_out_cells;\n    I64 row_tile_start;\n    I64 col_tile_start;\n    I64 row_tile_end;\n    I64 col_tile_end;\n    I64 row_index;\n    I64 col_index;\n    I64 lhs_row_base;\n    I64 rhs_col_base;\n    I64 out_row_base;\n    I64 out_index;\n    I64 cell_dot_q32;\n    Q4_0Block *lhs_row_ptr;\n    Q4_0Block *rhs_col_ptr;\n    I32 status;\n\n    if (!lhs_matrix_blocks || !rhs_col_blocks || !out_mat_q32)\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_NULL_PTR;\n\n    if (lhs_block_capacity < 0 || rhs_block_capacity < 0 || out_capacity < 0)\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n    if (lhs_rows < 0 || lhs_row_stride_blocks < 0)\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n    if (rhs_cols < 0 || rhs_col_stride_blocks < 0)\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n    if (k_block_count < 0 || out_row_stride_cols < 0)\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n    if (tile_rows <= 0 || tile_cols <= 0)\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n\n    // Active K span must fit in both row strides.\n    if (lhs_rows > 0 && lhs_row_stride_blocks < k_block_count)\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n    if (rhs_cols > 0 && rhs_col_stride_blocks < k_block_count)\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n\n    // Output stride must be wide enough for the active output columns.\n    if (lhs_rows > 0 && out_row_stride_cols < rhs_cols)\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n\n    // Capacity proofs for full strided views.\n    if (!Q4_0MatMulTryMulI64NonNeg(lhs_rows, lhs_row_stride_blocks, &required_lhs_blocks))\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_OVERFLOW;\n    if (!Q4_0MatMulTryMulI64NonNeg(rhs_cols, rhs_col_stride_blocks, &required_rhs_blocks))\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_OVERFLOW;\n    if (!Q4_0MatMulTryMulI64NonNeg(lhs_rows, out_row_stride_cols, &required_out_cells))\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_OVERFLOW;\n\n    if (required_lhs_blocks > lhs_block_capacity)\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n    if (required_rhs_blocks > rhs_block_capacity)\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n    if (required_out_cells > out_capacity)\n        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n\n    // Tile loops keep future AVX2 kernel boundaries explicit while routing\n    // each row/column dot through the checked row-dot primitive.\n    row_tile_start = 0;\n    while (row_tile_start < lhs_rows)\n    {\n        if (!Q4_0MatMulTryAddI64NonNeg(row_tile_start, tile_rows, &row_tile_end))\n            return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_OVERFLOW;\n        row_tile_end = Q4_0MatMulMinI64(row_tile_end, lhs_rows);\n\n        col_tile_start = 0;\n        while (col_tile_start < rhs_cols)\n        {\n            if (!Q4_0MatMulTryAddI64NonNeg(col_tile_start, tile_cols, &col_tile_end))\n                return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_OVERFLOW;\n            col_tile_end = Q4_0MatMulMinI64(col_tile_end, rhs_cols);\n\n            for (row_index = row_tile_start; row_index < row_tile_end; ++row_index)\n            {\n                if (!Q4_0MatMulTryMulI64NonNeg(row_index, lhs_row_stride_blocks, &lhs_row_base))\n                    return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_OVERFLOW;\n                if (!Q4_0MatMulTryMulI64NonNeg(row_index, out_row_stride_cols, &out_row_base))\n                    return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_OVERFLOW;\n\n                lhs_row_ptr = &lhs_matrix_blocks[lhs_row_base];\n\n                for (col_index = col_tile_start; col_index < col_tile_end; ++col_index)\n                {\n                    if (!Q4_0MatMulTryMulI64NonNeg(col_index, rhs_col_stride_blocks, &rhs_col_base))\n                        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_OVERFLOW;\n                    if (!Q4_0MatMulTryAddI64NonNeg(out_row_base, col_index, &out_index))\n                        return Q4_0_MATMUL_ERR_OVERFLOW;\n\n                    rhs_col_ptr = &rhs_col_blocks[rhs_col_base];\n\n                    // Use checked row-dot kernel with row_count=1.\n                    // This preserves the exact Q4_0 AVX2-shape arithmetic contract.\n                    status = Q4_0DotRowsAVX2Q32Checked(lhs_row_ptr,\n                                                       lhs_block_capacity - lhs_row_base,\n                                                       1,\n                                                       lhs_row_stride_blocks,\n                                                       rhs_col_ptr,\n       